message.content:
1. There was some improvement in dispenser knowledge.
2. There was no difference between arms in adherence measured as completion of all doses.
3. The completion rate of all doses in the intervention group was 68.3%.
4. The completion rate of all doses in the control group was 69.8%.
5. The adjusted p-value for the difference in completion of all doses between the groups was 0.6.
6. There was no difference between arms in adherence measured as completion of each dose at the correct time.
7. The completion rate of each dose at the correct time in the intervention group was 33.1%.
8. The completion rate of each dose at the correct time in the control group was 32.6%.
9. The adjusted p-value for the difference in completion of each dose at the correct time between the groups was 0.9.

messages.content:
Statement: Although there was some improvement in dispenser knowledge, there was no difference between arms in adherence measured as completion of all doses (intervention 68.3%, control 69.8%, p [adjusted] = 0.6), or as completion of each dose at the correct time (intervention 33.1%, control 32.6%, p [adjusted] = 0.9).
